OL,3,CTeenage boy 'died in terror' after dad
OL,4,Chigh on cocaine crashed van
OL,6,F"You chose to drive on a motorway on a
OL,7,Fbusy bank holiday Sunday. You had a
OL,8,Fpassenger in the van and that
OL,9,Fpassenger was your son, a person you
OL,10,Fshould have been protecting and not
OL,11,Fendangering.
OL,13,F"You knew that taking cocaine made
OL,14,Fyour decision to drive all the more
OL,15,Fdangerous. Your driving put many other
OL,16,Froad users in danger."
OL,18,FSpeaking outside court Sgt Martin
OL,19,FWilcock of Lancashire police said
OL,20,FRyan's death has had a lasting impact.
